  "label": "The Ironbound Locker",
  "description": "The Ironbound Locker serves as a compact storespace opening off the Ironband Passage, its timber walls cinched with riveted iron straps in the same siege-minded fashion as the corridor beyond. Tiered shelving and chain-secured racks line the bulkheads, leaving a narrow central aisle kept clear for rapid inventory and issue. Canvas-wrapped bins and tarred crates dominate the floor, their surfaces dulled by ash grit and sealed against damp. A shuttered lantern box throws a cold, disciplined light over devotional glyphs cut above the threshold, marking the room as regulated and sanctioned storage.",
